</cloze>

<question>
  I have one dog.

  <answer>
    Unum canem habeo.

    Canem habeo.

    "Canis" is a thrid declension noun.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  You have two dogs.

  <answer>
    Duos canes habes.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  I see three dogs.

  <answer>
    Tres canes video.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Quattour vaccae.

  <answer>
    Four cows.

    The numbers from 4 to 10 don't decline.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Quinque aves.

  <answer>
    Five birds.

    Singular of "aves" is "avis".
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Sex porci.

  <answer>
    Six pigs.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Septem leones.

  <answer>
    Seven lions.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Quinque aves et tres aves sunt octo aves.

  <answer>
    Five birds and three birds are eight birds.
  </answer>
</question>

<question>
  Quattour vaccae et quinque aves sunt novem animalia.

  <answer>
    Four cows and five birds are nine animals.
  </answer>
</question>

